# Phase 27: Pin/Unpin Auto-Hide for Library (Songs/Bible) Pane

Add VS Code-style auto-hide pin functionality to the Songs/Bible search pane only. A permanent slim icon rail on the left side provides toggle controls, and a pin icon in the pane's title bar controls the pin mode.

**Scope**: Library (Songs/Bible) pane only. Monitors pane is excluded (hiding it would break OBS capture surface).

## Interaction Model

The Library pane has two independent states:

| State | Values | Default |
|-------|--------|---------|
| **Pin Mode** | `pinned` / `autoHide` | `pinned` |
| **Visibility** | `visible` / `hidden` | `visible` |

### Always-Visible Left Icon Rail

A slim vertical rail (~32px wide) is **always visible** on the far left of the app, containing two icons:
- 🎵 Music icon (`Icons.library_music`) — for Songs tab
- 📖 Book icon (`Icons.menu_book`) — for Bible tab

The Library pane opens **to the right** of this rail.

### Behavior When Pinned (Default)

| Action | Result |
|--------|--------|
| Click rail icon for **same** active tab | Pane **hides** (stays pinned) |
| Click rail icon for **different** tab | Pane switches to that tab (stays visible) |
| Click rail icon when pane is **hidden** | Pane **opens** on that tab (stays open, stays pinned) |
| Click **pin icon** in pane title bar | Mode changes to `autoHide`, pane **hides** |

In pinned mode, the pane is **docked** — it occupies layout space (flex-based) and other panes adjust around it.

### Behavior When Auto-Hide (Unpinned)

| Action | Result |
|--------|--------|
| Click rail icon when pane is **hidden** | Pane opens **as an overlay** on that tab |
| Click rail icon when pane is **visible** (overlay) | Pane **hides** |
| Click **elsewhere** (outside the overlay pane) | Pane **hides** |
| Click **pin icon** in pane title bar (while overlay is open) | Mode changes back to `pinned`, pane **docks** into layout |

In auto-hide mode, the pane opens as a **floating overlay** (does NOT shift layout of Setlist/Slides). This ensures the layout doesn't jump around with each temporary open/close.

### Pin Icon Visual States

| Mode | Icon | Tooltip |
|------|------|---------|
| Pinned | `Icons.push_pin` (filled, vertical) | "Unpin (Auto Hide)" |
| Auto-Hide | `Icons.push_pin_outlined` (rotated 45°) | "Pin" |

### Keyboard Shortcuts

- `Q` key: Opens Songs tab + un-hides pane (regardless of pin mode). If in auto-hide mode, acts as if user clicked the Songs rail icon.
- `S` key: Opens Bible tab + un-hides pane (regardless of pin mode). If in auto-hide mode, acts as if user clicked the Bible rail icon.

## Assumptions

> [!NOTE]
> **Rail icon highlight**: The currently active tab's rail icon will have a subtle highlight (e.g., left border accent or background tint) when the pane is visible, matching VS Code's Activity Bar behavior. This is minimal and only for indicating which tab is active.

> [!NOTE]
> **Overlay dimensions in auto-hide mode**: When the pane opens as an overlay, it will match its original docked width (same flex-8 equivalent, approximately 40% of available width). The overlay will have a subtle drop shadow on its right edge to visually distinguish it from the content behind.

> [!NOTE]
> **No state persistence**: The pin mode will NOT be persisted to disk. On app restart, the pane defaults back to pinned + visible. If you want persistence, let me know and I'll add it.

